{
  "doc_id": "40138",
  "text": "The precise mechanism of the pathogenesis of breast MALT is not known; however, there is a hypothesis that sex hormones modulate immune function and the development of NHL. Nevertheless, findings concerning the specific role of estrogen in the development of NHL as a whole are mixed; some studies have found no effect, while others have found a protective or contributory effect [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Further research on the proliferative effects of estrogen in malignant conditions could be beneficial in the development of new treatments; there is some current evidence to support the proposition that estrogen receptor may modulate the proliferative effects of estrogen receptor [CITATION_4] . Further research on the balance between proliferative (ER ) and antiproliferative (ER ) effects of estrogen receptors could lead to new NHL cancer treatments.",
